configSetPrices.disclaimer:
For EU Orders
  • Tesla Motors Netherlands B.V. (“Tesla”) will not arrange any shipping for your car. You are responsible for coordinating pick up of your vehicle from our Tilburg Factory in the Netherlands (within one week of vehicle’s readiness).
  • The sale to other EU countries will be subject to the 0% VAT rate in the Netherlands, provided that customer will provide Tesla within 30 days after supply with the relevant documents to support the application of the 0% VAT rate in the Netherlands.
  • The following documents are requested from customer:
    • signed VAT declaration (to be provided by Tesla upon delivery) as well as
    • proof of registration of the vehicle in the destination country. If the vehicle has been transported by a carrier, a copy of the signed CMR will be required as well.
  • If the above documents are not provided with the agreed timeframe, Tesla is entitled (and customer will accept) an adjusted invoice with the VAT amount due on the sale.
  • Tesla Ranger Service may be available upon request, pending availability, and is not guaranteed. Tesla Ranger Service may not be available in certain markets or to certain locations. Tesla Ranger Service will only be performed if there is a suitable facility available. Certain operations cannot be performed by a Tesla Ranger and will require the return of the vehicle to an authorized Tesla Service Center. At any time, Tesla reserves the right to deny Tesla Ranger Service and require the vehicle to be returned to an authorized Tesla Service Center.
  • When your car needs to return to a Tesla Service Center to receive service, you will be responsible for arranging and paying for transport.
For Russia, Turkey & Iceland Orders
  • Tesla Motors Netherlands B.V. (“Tesla”) will not arrange any shipping for your car. You are responsible for coordinating pick up of your vehicle from our Tilburg Factory in the Netherlands (within one week of vehicle’s readiness).
  • Tesla will file an export declaration from the Netherlands.
  • The export sale will be subject to the 0% VAT rate in the Netherlands, provided that customer will provide Tesla within 30 days after supply with proof-of-export documents.
  • The proof-of-export documents consist of:
    • signed CMR for transport from the Netherlands to destination country.
    • copy of import documents into destination country or proof of registration in destination country.
  • If the above documents are not provided with the agreed timeframe, Tesla is entitled (and customer will accept) an adjusted invoice with the Netherlands VAT amount due on the sale.
  • You will be solely responsible for importing the car in your country, including payment of any duties and fees and compliance with local import regulations, as well as for transportation of the car from the Netherlands to your destination.
  • Service parts and Accessories are shipped centrally from the Netherlands, and will be sold to you including shipping costs to your destination. You will be solely responsible for importing the goods in your country, including payment of any duties and fees and compliance with local import regulations
  • This vehicle is sold in the Tesla European Warranty Region and the New Vehicle Limited Warranty applies. For the purposes of the New Vehicle Limited Warranty, the Tesla European Warranty Region is defined the Member States of the European Economic Area. In order to receive warranty service, you must transport the vehicle to a Tesla Service Centre in the country in which the vehicle was originally purchased from Tesla. You will be responsible for all transport costs to and from the Tesla Service Centre.
  • Tesla provides no warranties regarding the ability to import or register the car in your country, nor the ability to import other Tesla goods into your country.
  • Tesla Ranger Service may not be available in your country. Vehicles located in countries where Ranger Service is not available cannot be serviced by Tesla onsite and must be returned to an authorized Tesla Service Center to receive service. If available in your country, Tesla Ranger Service is available upon request, pending availability, and is not guaranteed. Tesla Ranger Service may not be available in certain markets or to certain locations. Tesla Ranger Service will only be performed if there is a suitable facility available. Certain operations cannot be performed by a Tesla Ranger and will require the return of the vehicle to an authorized Tesla Service Center. At any time, Tesla reserves the right to deny Tesla Ranger Service and require the vehicle to be returned to an authorized Tesla Service Center.
  • When your car needs to return to a Tesla Service Center to receive service, you will be solely responsible for any applicable export/import formalities in your country. You will responsible for transportation to and from the Service Center nominated by Tesla, and will be liable for transport costs as well as any duties, taxes and fees that may become due.
  • Tesla European specification vehicles have been homologated and configured to operate within Tesla-designated Core Markets. Some features and functions, including, but not limited to, data connectivity, navigation maps, driver assistance, and vehicle charging may not function properly or at all in countries or regions other than the ones for which European specification vehicles have been designed and homologated. Tesla does not provide support for modifying vehicles, existing installations, or other property to meet different specifications, other than the installation of a data SIM card for vehicle data connectivity. Such no-Tesla SIM cards must be provided by the customer prior to delivery of the new vehicle, and a Non-Tesla SIM Card Waiver must be signed by the customer.


There are different advantages to the 21-inch and 19-inch wheels. For example, the 21-inch wheels generally provide increased handling whereas the 19-inch wheels wear less quickly and provide more protection from obstacles and poor road conditions.

The information presented on this website is based on data available at the time. Design, specifications, price, and production dates are subject to change without notice and pertain specifically to European vehicles. Some features and options may be unavailable when your vehicle enters production.

WTW2.name: 19” Nokian Winter Wheel Set

X019.description: Improve high speed stability by adding the carbon fiber spoiler to your trunk lid. Made from lightweight, cross-woven carbon fibers with a matte epoxy finish.

PSP14.description: Annual service includes an inspection every 20,000 kilometers, replacement parts like brake pads and windshield wipers, 24 hour roadside assistance, and remote diagnostics.

PA01.name: No Paint Armor
PA01.description:
Protect key areas of Model S against stone chips, bug damage, weathering and other paint damage. Paint Armor is clear film that is applied to:
  • Exterior mirrors
  • Front bumper, fascia and hood (nose)
  • Front and rear fender (trailing edge)
  • Front and rear rocker panels
  • Rear bumper fascia

Depending on the angle of sunlight, seams between protected and unprotected paint areas will be visible, particularly on white and pearl white cars.

PX01.name: Performance Plus
PX01.description: Performance Plus adds world class handling to the incredible acceleration of Model S Performance, while also improving range. After hundreds of iterations affecting every detail of the suspension, our vehicle dynamics team was able to achieve the rare outcome of improving both performance and efficiency. In addition to upgraded dampers, bushings, stabilizer bars and tires (Michelin Pilot Sport PS2), the rear tires are 20 mm wider and staggered for improved acceleration on low grip surfaces. Range improves 10 to 20 kilometers over regular 21” wheels.

SU01.name: Smart Air Suspension
SU01.description: Automatically adjusts stiffness for optimum performance and ride regardless of road surface or cargo. Location aware, the air suspension automatically re-applies manual settings each time it nears previous GPS coordinates, particularly useful for steep driveways.

The Tech Package adds Autopilot convenience features and more to an already advanced car.

Autopilot features are made available through progressive software updates. Lane keeping and self-parking updates will be available soon.
